  <div class="page">
    <p>Conclusions and perspectives</p>
    <p>Robustness is an important issue in timed systems</p>
    <p>timed automata are governed by a mathematical semantics;</p>
    <p>this raises important robustness issues:</p>
    <p>time-convergent behaviours; strict timing constraints...</p>
    <p>several approaches:</p>
    <p>ignoring isolated traces; considering surrounding runs.</p>
    <p>Perspectives</p>
    <p>develop the quantitative approach to robustness;</p>
    <p>probabilistic (as opposed to worst-case) enlargement;</p>
    <p>shrinking timed automata (to counteract enlargement);</p>
    <p>robust controller synthesis;</p>
    <p>robustness in priced timed automata (with energy constraints).</p>
  </div>
